entries.title: Cruise ship passengers stranded at sea for days after 'biofoul' discovered
entries.description: Cruise ship passengers have been stranded at sea for nearly a week after "biofoul" growth was discovered on the hull - with Australian officials refusing permission for it to dock.

entries.title: Lula da Silva sworn in as Brazil president
entries.description: Brazil officially has a new but familiar president as Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva was sworn in for the third time.

entries.title: 'We will just live our lives': Ukrainians insist on celebrating New Year despite curfews and missile strikes
entries.description: Picture this - New Year's Eve in Kyiv's St Sophia's Cathedral square.

entries.title: Man carrying explosive device and knife arrested at inauguration of Brazil's new president
entries.description: A man carrying an explosive device and a knife has been arrested while attempting to enter the inauguration of Brazil's new president, according to military police.

entries.title: Four human skulls wrapped in tin foil discovered at Mexican airport
entries.description: Four human skulls have been discovered inside a package at a Mexican airport that was headed to the US by courier.

entries.title: Andrew Tate's Twitter account used to protest his innocence after human trafficking arrest
entries.description: Andrew Tate's Twitter account has been used to protest the influencer's innocence after he was arrested on suspicion of human trafficking.

entries.title: Australia grapples with worker shortage after strict COVID rules
entries.description: Australia is reviewing its entire visa and immigration system in an all-out effort to rapidly increase its workforce.

entries.title: Terror probe after machete attack near New York's New Year celebrations - suspect shot
entries.description: Specialist terrorism experts are investigating an attack involving a machete on police in New York that left three officers hurt.

entries.title: Idaho student murders suspect was allegedly warned after making 'creepy' comments
entries.description: A man accused of killing four students in the US was warned after making "creepy" and inappropriate comments to staff and customers at a brewery, its owner has claimed.

entries.title: Pope Francis prays for Benedict as Vatican prepares to mourn former pontiff
entries.description: Pope Francis has prayed for his predecessor Benedict XVI at a special New Year's Day Mass.

entries.title: Australia and Canada are the latest to announce COVID-19 travel rules for arrivals from China
entries.description: Australia and Canada are the latest countries to bring in travel restrictions on arrivals from China.

entries.title: Kim calls for 'exponential' increase in North Korea's nuclear arsenal
entries.description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un says he wants to increase the country's nuclear arsenal "exponentially".
